The Independent Cross Sections were Calculated Taking
Into Account the Measured Cumulative Cross Sections
Of the Observed Nuclides and Those of Their Precursors.
Yields of Radioactive I and Te were Calculated For
Protons of 540 MeV Based on the Collection of the
Xe Gases. The Practicality of Producing I-123 and
I-127 with High Energy Protons is Discussed.
Additional Experiments were Performed to Account
For Interfering Activities and Varying Beam Conditions.

Na-22 Data was 10-20 Per Cent (NA-24) And 5-15 Per Cent

Energy Secondary Particles. To Minimize Their Influence
On the Measured Cross Sections,the Authors Used the
Na-24 Data For Beam Monitoring,Since They Felt That
